category: BIBLICAL ZOO
category comment: 

clue: Symbolic animals in the KJV include the dragon & this single-horned animal mentioned in Numbers 23:22

response: a unicorn

clue: The Old Testament talks about the jungle on the Jordan's banks & this animal roaring within

response: a lion

clue: Samson caught 300 of these sly creatures, put firebrands on their tails & sent them into enemy cornfields

response: foxes

clue: According to Deuteronomy 17:1, if your bullock is blemished you can't use it as this

response: a sacrifice

clue: After crossing this, Miriam led a chorus of "the horse and his rider hath he thrown into the sea"

response: the Red Sea

